    "text": "<@U03LMRE6MQE> its common to use protobuff messages in databases and files in Google. They don't always go over the wire. They are a serialization format, similarly, I don't see a problem with JSON not going over the wire, and swagger is a reasonable IDL for JSON. Not sure where its getting weird for you, does it insist you put things on paths or its not possible to collect the data object from the server stubs or something? Conceptually it's a reasonable usecase to me.",
